Hello everyone! I am organizing a FREE dreamboarding session in celebration of SG60, as a community partner or Dream Big Singapore (https://dreambigsingapore.sg). We are on an ambitious project to collect 6000 dreamboards for Singapore’s 60th birthday, by asking a simple question “What is your dream?” It will be a very simple workshop - like session that last for about 30 minutes. For makan(refreshments), we will be supporting local vendors so you can look forward to delicious treats! Please sign up using the link to secure your spot now!

https://forms.gle/GFenmBBj7iL8y9Rn7

🚀 Wondering how venture capital can open doors — even beyond a career in VC?

Join us for Protégé Ventures Info Session II and hear from alumni who’ve gone on to careers in tech, finance, consulting, and more.

What to expect:
🔹 Real stories from alumni
🔹 What you’ll actually do as a PV analyst
🔹 How PV builds real-world skills like startup evaluation and strategic thinking

You’ll also learn how PV offers exclusive internship opportunities and 1-on-1 access to mentors and industry leaders — experiences that help launch strong careers.

📅 Date: 2nd July (Wednesday)
🕖 Time: 7:00 PM
📍 Venue: SMU School of Law, Level 4 Function Room

🎟 Limited slots — reserve now:
👉 REGISTER HERE: https://lu.ma/nzd5wnx1

About Protégé Ventures (PV):

PV is Singapore’s first and only student-run venture fund, where students gain hands-on VC experience.

Open to all students from polytechnics and universities!

📝 RECRUITMENT open till 18 July!
Apply here: bit.ly/Apply_PV2025
